<body>
    <h1>Instructions</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Click the <b>Set Boys or Girls Text File</b> button. Name a file for either boys' or girls' times, depending on which race is going first.
        </li>
        <li class="sub-item">
            Click the <b>Open XC Merged Results</b> button. This will open the Merged Results Program.
            <div class="sub-item">
                <b>XC Merged Results Program</b>
                <ol>
                    <li>Allows you to use a Milesplit CSV entries file for easy scoring setup.</li>
                    <li>Converts the Milesplit CSV entries to only have the TEAM | ATHLETE NAME | GENDER.</li>
                    <li>
                        Open the CC_Scorer:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Adds a Bib column to identify the athlete.</li>
                            <li>Enter bibs as athletes finish (use one laptop to enter bibs).</li>
                            <li>Copy and Paste the Times from the text created on the XC Webcam Stopwatch program.</li>
                            <li>With the bibs and times, the XC_Scorer will automatically score a cross-country meet for athletes and teams.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </li>
        <li>Click the <b>Start Video Capture</b> button. This will bring up at least one webcam display with an overlaid timer (stopwatch).</li>
        <li>
            Click the <b>Start Timer</b> button. This will start the stopwatch timer. You can also press the Spacebar to start the timer, but the cursor must be on the webcam display for this to work.
        </li>
        <li>
            Click the <b>Start Screen Recording</b> button. This will record your desktop's screen and save it as an AVI file, which you will be prompted to name. This is a way to review time and athletes' finishes if athletes are wearing bibs.
        </li>
        <li>
            Once a race is finished, click the buttons in the following order:
            <ol>
                <li>Click <b>Stop Screen Recording</b> to stop the screen recording.</li>
                <li>Click <b>Stop Timer</b> to stop the stopwatch timer from running.</li>
                <li>Click <b>Stop Video Capture</b> to close the webcam displays.</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>Click the <b>Quit</b> button to close the program.</li>
    </ol>
</body>
</html>
